==============================================================
2. Vigenere Cipher
==============================================================

Compile using:
make vigenere

Run using:
./vigeneredecoder FILE.txt
where FILE.txt is the name of the file to be decoded

-------------------------------------------------------------
a) Repeating Patterns
-PVV Distances between repetitions: 64, 80, 84, 92, 100
-RZZ Distances between repetitions: 8
-CEEK Distances between repetitions: 196
-------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------
b) Possible lengths
The common factors between the distances mentioned in 
part (a) are 1, 2, and 4. So the possible lengths of the key
are:
- 1
- 2
- 4
-------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------
c) Decoded string. The program which uses a key length of 4
can be found in vigeneredecoder.cpp

